        "description": {
            "value": "<p>As a swashbuckler, you have your own distinctive style that enables you to gracefully handle everyday events and life-or-death situations alike. Choose a swashbuckler's style. This style determines the additional actions you use to gain panache and makes you trained in the skill related to that action.</p>\n<p>You are friendly, clever, and full of humor, always knowing just what to say in any situation. Your witticisms leave foes unprepared for the skill and speed of your attacks.</p>\n<p>You are trained in Diplomacy and gain the @Compendium[pf2e.feats-srd.Bon Mot]{Bon Mot} skill feat. You gain @Compendium[pf2e.classfeatures.Panache]{Panache} during an encounter whenever you succeed at a Bon Mot against a foe.</p>"
